qas.question: What community does the Tribune serve?
What paper serves the LGBT community?

context: The city also has a number of other, smaller newspapers and magazine in circulation such as the <a0_0>Philadelphia Tribune<a0_0/>, which serves the <a1_0>African-American community<a1_0/>, the Philadelphia, a monthly regional magazine; Philadelphia Weekly, an weekly-printed alternative newspaper; Philadelphia City Paper another weekly-printed newspaper; <a2_0>Philadelphia Gay News<a2_0/>, which services the LGBT community; <a3_0>The Jewish Exponent<a3_0/> a weekly-printed newspaper servicing the Jewish community; Philadelphia Metro, free daily newspaper; and Al Día, a weekly newspaper servicing the Latino community.
